	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Halflings are neat. I went on the sites and looked up the statistics for all the different types of clerics and read how much better statistic  - wise it was to play a dwarf cleric instead of a Halfling cleric. (There&#8217;s a whole school of thought to this &#8211; high elf has high wisdom, therefore more mana at early levels {Wisdom equipment tends to make this a lesser issue in later levels}, Dwarves have higher strength and therefore can do more damage per blow in battle and can carry more, dark elves are despised or simply Killed On Sight (KOS) in some places))  read and contemplated this information. Then I chucked it all out of the window and played what I wanted to play. Here's my take on this wonderful race. <BR>
<BR>
1. Halflings rise in level quicker than any other race (except for humans.) Humans are OK but they can&#8217;t see in the dark and they have no special skills to speak of.  <BR>
<BR>
2. A Halflings high agility and dexterity will directly result in getting more hits  in with your weapons, more weapon &quot;procs&quot;(&quot;procs&quot; stands for process - a weapon with a magical ability determines when to process that ability using your dexterity as a modifier) and the oh so important &#8220;not getting hit so much&#8221; when you&#8217;re in battle fact. <BR>
More hits landing faster  = more damage = monster dies sooner rather than later and you can kill more. <BR>
Getting hit less often = decreased down time = being able to kill again sooner rather than later.<BR>
Also  when you are grouped, the healer has to heal the damaged people in the party. <BR>
If you aren&#8217;t getting damaged as much, the healer has more mana to go around and the party can fight longer before the healer has to med. <BR>
  <BR>
3. Halflings are insanely fast. We run fast (comes in handy when your running from a monster or if you have to run 5 or 6 zones and can't get a Sprit of the Wolf from a nice druid or shaman.) <BR>
Halflings fight fast, too.  This comes in handy cause you kill stuff fast. (This also comes in handy when you see you are hitting much faster than your ogre chum is. It&#8217;s good to point this out every now and then too : ) <BR>
A side effect of all that fast hitting is more damage = more experience = fast leveling. <BR>
<BR>
4. Halflings eat fast too. I believe Halflings eat more per day than other races. ( Being a cleric - I can summon food and water so I've never noticed. Please correct me if I&#8217;m wrong.) <BR>
<BR>
5. All Halflings have sneak and hide - which are rogue skills. As a druid or cleric , they never increase, though . Hide does have its advantages. ( Hide &#8211; meditate  - no monsters attack you.) Since the skill level is low though, it doesn't work all the time. You can ask a nearby person if they can see you - or you can &quot;right click&#8221; a hostile monster. If it goes &quot;indifferent&quot; after you hide, then it worked.  You can also use sneak to trade with merchants who will not trade with you. (Hit &quot;sneak&quot; /con merchant &#8211; it should con &#8220;indifferent&#8221; / and then you can make your trade. <BR>
<BR>
6. Halflings have low charisma - which is a shame because the Halflings in stories are such likable fellows. However this can be remedied by several items in the game &#8211; squad ring, steins, etc.&#8230;<BR>
<BR>
7. Rivervale is an intense city to start out in. <BR>
It's easily maneuverable  and lots of high level players tend to hang here. Most of them  will buff you for free if you ask nicely. Some will even give you free equipment. There are places in town that sell food and water. There is a girl, with a tiny stall close to the cleric's guild. She sells water. Find the  bag merchant  - the dock merchant sitting beside him sells fish cakes. These are a little pricey 1 silver and a few copper but last a long time. Also if you get into dire straits if you do a /shout or  /ooc&quot; Can someone loan me some food? &quot;  some one most likely will. <BR>
Don&#8217;t fall into the water at low levels. Piranha will eat you alive. There is also a quest MOB fish in the water. It will eat you alive too.   For giggles buy a Fool&#8217;s gold stein from the Fool&#8217;s Gold Tavern <BR>
It looks vaguely familiar to a stein of Mogguk (which is somewhat rare) and people will think you are rich. It&#8217;s great for getting hammered too. <BR>
<BR>
8. When you&#8217;ve had your fun, go outside to Misty Thicket and kill snakes and bats and spiders and what not . Kill anything that cons blue. (Heck everything cons blue at level 1. ) Don&#8217;t kill Ember &#8211; Blixxen&#8217;s pet spider. Blix will kill you in a few hits  when you&#8217;re a few levels up , take the left from the Misty Thicket gate and cross over the wall into the harder territory. There are guards here and their MOB aggro sensitivity is quite high. (Some say too high.) If you get in trouble run for the guards. If you hit the guards, pray you have SOW and run for Rivervale. Look out for Mooto. Mooto is a named Goblin  that spawns in the goblin camp  and walks over to the  orc camp. Mooto is fast/casts spells  and is dangerous for low levels. <BR>
Sometimes he has a nice lower level item if you can take him out. <BR>
<BR>
Once your level 10,11, 12 or so things might get a little tiresome.  Do not go to Kithicor forest to level. Kithicor  Forest is level 45+ at night and some MOBS have a +600 harm touch spell and can out run SOW.  Do Not go into Runnyeye without thinking about it first. Actually I&#8217;ve never done it. I&#8217;ve HEARD a party of 23 &#8216;s can do well there. The bad thing is (I&#8217;ve been barely inside -  LOL)  is that the goblins run at half health and then they bring 5 of their buddies. It&#8217;s not pretty. Goblins stun and all. <BR>
If you  go to the Kithicor forest take a left and run to the Commons. The Commons (with its&#8217; spiders/bears/and dervish cutthroats are quite fun.  I played there from 12 to 16 or so and then ran to Oasis to kill orcs. After that I got a teleport to Faydwer and then took the boat from crushbone to Kunark to Lake of Ill Omen. There are other good places to level as well. Ask your guild or ask around. <BR>
<BR>
9. One thing I&#8217;ve noticed about Halflings is that we are short. Real short. If you want to walk around and look at people&#8217;s butts all day in Full screen 1st person mode, then this is the race for you. <BR>
Also it can get confusing in fights as Trolls and Ogres can block your vision in regards to monsters. Something to keep in mind. <BR>
<BR>
10. Halflings don&#8217;t really have a problem (initially)  traveling  on the main continent. Their city is centrally located and it&#8217;s a quick run to most places. <BR>
<BR>
11. Halflings are  darn cute. People love hairy feet.<BR>
<BR>
12. One thing I forgot to mention about Rivervale is there are some quite good quests there. It&#8217;s possible to make the first 3 levels there fairly quickly doing nothing but quests .. over and over and over&#8230;. <BR>
Well this is Ever Quest right? If you need help .. Just tune in to this site choose the maps section .. The quests are listed there.  It is also possible for some evil races to hang out in the city if they kill enough Goblins. I&#8217;ve seen Ogres, Trolls, and Dark elves in the city. I&#8217;ve even seen an Iksar once. Killing a quest mob inside the city. Anything&#8217;s possible if you get your faction up enough. It shouldn&#8217;t take more than 300 goblins and orcs from what I&#8217;ve head. (Never tried this BTW.) <BR>
<BR>
Well that&#8217;s all I have.  Have fun with your Halfling! <BR>
<BR>
Sassii<BR>
The Nameless<BR>
 <BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
